 \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ -1 & 1 \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} x \\ 1/x \end{pmatrix}\\ = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix} \frac{1 + x^2}{x}\\ \frac{1 - x^2}{x} \end{pmatrix}. 
 \frac{1}{2a^2}\left(\frac{x^4 + 2x^2 + 1}{x^2}\right) - \frac{1}{2b^2}\left(\frac{x^4 - 2x^2 + 1}{x^2}\right) = 1 \\ \implies b^2(x^4 + 2x^2 + 1) - a^2(x^4 - 2x^2 + 1) = 2a^2b^2x^2. 
